      "content": "Those symptoms sound like your asthma is flaring up again, which is common for adults as their lungs naturally lose some elasticity with age. You should definitely see a doctor soon to adjust your inhaler or add a new medication rather than just assuming it's normal aging. While some breathing changes are part of getting older, sudden shortness of breath during minimal activity usually indicates your current treatment isn't working well enough.",
